 designed a questionnaire to collect data on prevalence and management of hemolytic specimens referred to the clinical laboratories for clinical chemistry testing. This book will help identify the areas where hemolysis occurs most frequently, which can, in turn, guide further analysis about why it is occurring. Once these elements are known, practices and procedures can be implemented to dramatically reduce hemolysis and avoid erroneous laboratory results affecting patient care and increasing laboratory costs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBloodxExamination. 0aHematologyxStandards. 4aHämolyse. 4aLabormedizin. 4aNotfallmedizin. 7aMEDICAL / Laboratory Medicine.2bisacsh  aEmergency Medical Aid.  aHemolysis.  aLaboratory Medicine.1 aCervellin, Gianfranco, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFavaloro, Emmanuel J., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPlebani, Mario, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Medicine and Life Sciences 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023849508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Medicine and Life Sciences 2000 - 2014z9783110637915oZDB-23-GML08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE  MEDICINE 2012z9783110293807oZDB-23-DME08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET MEDIZIN 2012z9783110293791oZDB-23-DMD0 cprintz978311024613140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311024614840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110246148423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover